                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-off1396" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18300916-275-cd1397" type="crimeDate">17th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-275-off1396 t18300916-275-cd1397"></join>, 1 sovereign, the money of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18300916-275-victim2270" type="victimName">
                           Richard 
                           Payne
                        <interp inst="t18300916-275-victim2270" type="surname" value="Payne"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18300916-275-victim2270" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18300916-275-victim2270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-275-off1396 t18300916-275-victim2270"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>RICHARD PAYNE. On the 17th of July I was in <placeName id="t18300916-275-crimeloc1398">Union-street, Hackney-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-275-crimeloc1398" type="placeName" value="Union-street, Hackney-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-275-crimeloc1398" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-275-off1396 t18300916-275-crimeloc1398"></join>, at half-past eleven o'clock in the evening - I had been to a hard week's work, and took a little drop of drink; I had fallen asleep in the street- I had changed a sovereign just before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-275-person2271">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2271" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2271" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2271" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner in the White Bear gardens, at half-past eleven o'clock at night; the prosecutor was lying on the ground, and the prisoner persuaded him to get up, but he would not - there was another row; I went, saw the prisoner go over to the prosecutor, help him up, and they fell down together - the prisoner then got up again, took the sovereign out of the prosecutor's pocket, and put it into his own; he asked me what it was - I said a sovereign; he said it was better in his pocket than in the prosecutor's - he said so help him God he should have it to-morrow; the prosecutor said,"It is all over, it is all over," and then he went away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-275-person2272">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HARTGA
               <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2272" type="surname" value="HARTGA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2272" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2272" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going by, and saw the prisoner take something from the prosecutor and put it into his left-hand pocket - the prosecutor said it was all over, and went away; the prisoner said so help him God he would give it him the next morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-275-person2273">
                  HENRY 
                  SOMES
               <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2273" type="surname" value="SOMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2273" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2273" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a publican. The prisoner came to change a sovereign with me, and the officer came and took him - he said he had picked it up in the street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-275-person2274">
                  GEORGE 
                  COLLYER
               <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2274" type="surname" value="COLLYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2274" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-person2274" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner at the Gentleman and Porter - he offered me the change; I said, "I want the sovereign;" the landlord said, "This is the sovereign" - I made him give the change back; he paid the 1 1/2d. for a glass of gin out of his own money.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming home, and the good man was laying down asleep, very much in liquor - the two boys were trying to lift him up; I tried to lift him, but could not - I took the sovereign, and said I would keep it till the morning; I told the boys where I had lived for thirty-five years.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300916-275-verdict1399" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-verdict1399" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 65. - <rs id="t18300916-275-punish1400" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-275-punish1400" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-275-defend2268 t18300916-275-punish1400"></join>
               Confined Fourteen Days
            </rs>.</p>
